Title: Fermionic Path Integrals and Analytic Solutions for Two-Dimensional

Ising ModelsAuthors: V.N. Plechko (Bogoliubov Lab Dubna)

Comments: LaTeX, 1 + 5 pages, no figures. A talk given at the 5th International

Conference on Path Integrals from meV to MeV, PI-96, Dubna, May 27--31, 1996Journal-ref: Proceedings PI-96 (JINR, Dubna, 1996) 295--299

The notion of the integral over the anticommuting Grassmann variables(nonquantum fermionic fields) seems to be the most powerful tool in order toextract the exact analytic solutions for the 2D Ising models on simple and morecomplicated lattices, which is the subject of a discussion in this report.